he  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McClammy","meanings":["Scottish: patronymic from a pet form of   Lamont  ."]},{"name":"McClymont","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Laomuinn</b> ‘son of <i>Laomann</i>’, a personal name borrowed from Old Norse and meaning ‘law giver’. See   Lamont  ."]},{"name":"Lemond","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  .","French: variant of <b>Lemonde</b>, a nickname from Old French <i>monde</i> ‘pure’, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>.","French (<b>Lémond</b>): variant of <b>Laymond</b>, itself a variant, with fused definite article <i>l'</i>, of   Aymond  ."]},{"name":"Lemont","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  .","French: habitational name from Le Mont in the Vosges or possibly other minor places so named from Old French <i>mont</i> ‘mountain’. Alternatively, a variant of   Lemond   2."]},{"name":"Lemonds","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  , with English excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Lawman","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Lamont  .","English: occupational name from Middle English <i>lagman</i>, <i>lagheman</i> ‘law-man, one whose duty is to declare the law; lawyer’ (Old Norse <i>lagmann-</i>, <i>lǫgmann-</i>, oblique case of <i>lǫgmathr</i>). The word was also widely used as a personal name, Middle English <i>Lagman</i>, <i>Lagheman</i>."]},{"name":"Lamond","meanings":["Scottish, northern Irish, and French: variant of   Lamont  . This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Lamothe","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Jacques, Pierre, Donat, Francois, Lucien, Odette, Adrien, Andree, Armand, Armande.","French: variant of   Lamotte  , or a habitational name from any of the places in France named Lamothe or La Mothe.","History: The settlement that became the city of Detroit was founded in 1701 by Antoine de la Mothe, Sieur de Cadillac (1658–1730), governor of LA. He was born into the minor nobility in Gascony, France, where his father owned the seigneury of Cadillac."]},{"name":"Lamonte","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lamont  ."]}]},{"name":"Laumon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Laumann  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Laumann","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Heinz, Kurt, Manfred, Otto, Wilhelm.","German: variant of   Lau  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Laumon Lamont 1st Chief of Clan Lamont was born about 1235, in Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Malcolm MacFerchar - Lord of Cowall, was 55 and his mother, Beatrice Somerled, was 51. He had at least 1 son with Lady Jean de Lyons. He died in 1293, in his hometown, at the age of 59, and was buried in Argyll, Scotland."},"et":{"Abt 1235–1293":"umbes 1235–1293","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1250–1294":"1250–1294","1181–1235":"1181–1235","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","Abt 1235":"umbes 1235","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1181":"1181","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"Abt 1235–1293":"noin 1235–1293","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1250–1294":"1250–1294","1181–1235":"1181–1235","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","Abt 1235":"noin 1235","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1181":"1181","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lamont, Argyll, Scotland":"Lamont, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"Abt 1235–1293":"environ 1235–1293","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1235–1293":"1235–1293","1215–Female":"1215–Décédée","